png2vtf
=======

A small utility that converts a PNG file into a Valve Texture Format
(VTF) file suitable for use as a Left 4 Dead 2 / Source Engine spray.

By default `png2vtf` accepts an ordinary PNG of any dimensions, scales
it proportionally to fit inside a 256x256 canvas, centers it with
transparent padding, and writes a full-color VTF using
`IMAGE_FORMAT_BGRA8888`. Both RGB and RGBA PNGs are accepted; if the
PNG has no alpha channel, fully opaque alpha is added automatically.

The legacy alpha-only behavior (`IMAGE_FORMAT_A8`) is still available
behind the `--format a8` flag, but it is **no longer the default**:
A8 stores only the alpha channel and is unusable as a normal visible
spray.


Dependencies
============

A C compiler, `make`, `pkg-config`, and `libpng` are required. No
ImageMagick, no CMake, no extra runtime tools.

Arch Linux:

    sudo pacman -S base-devel libpng pkgconf

Debian / Ubuntu:

    sudo apt install build-essential libpng-dev pkg-config

Fedora:

    sudo dnf install gcc make libpng-devel pkgconf-pkg-config


Build
=====

    make

This uses `pkg-config` to discover the compiler and linker flags for
`libpng`, so no manual configuration is required on a normal Linux
system.


Usage
=====

The simple default flow just works on any PNG:

    ./png2vtf input.png myspray.vtf

What this does automatically:

* decodes the PNG (RGB, RGBA, grayscale, palette, anything libpng
  understands) and converts it to RGBA;
* scales it proportionally with bilinear filtering to fit inside a
  256x256 canvas;
* centers it on a transparent canvas (no distortion);
* writes a full-color BGRA8888 VTF with the correct flags for use as
  an L4D2 spray.

You no longer need to pre-resize, pre-pad, or force the input to a
power-of-two size by hand.

Optional flags:

    ./png2vtf --size 512 input.png output.vtf       # 512x512 canvas
    ./png2vtf --fit contain input.png output.vtf    # default
    ./png2vtf --fit cover   input.png output.vtf    # crop to fill
    ./png2vtf --fit stretch input.png output.vtf    # distort to fill
    ./png2vtf --format bgra8888 input.png out.vtf   # default
    ./png2vtf --format rgba8888 input.png out.vtf
    ./png2vtf --format a8       input.png out.vtf   # legacy

`--size` accepts powers of two (e.g. `64`, `128`, `256`, `512`) to
match the VTF format requirement that texture dimensions be powers
of two.

Fit modes:

* `contain` (default) — preserve aspect ratio, fit the entire image
  into the canvas, transparent padding around the short side.
* `cover` — preserve aspect ratio, fill the canvas, crop overflow.
* `stretch` — resize directly to the canvas, may distort.


L4D2 spray workflow
===================

1. Build:

       make

2. Convert your PNG to a full-color VTF spray (any input dimensions
   work):

       ./png2vtf input.png myspray.vtf

3. Place the resulting file at:

       left4dead2/materials/vgui/logos/custom/myspray.vtf

4. Create a matching `myspray.vmt` next to it:

       "UnlitGeneric"
       {
           "$basetexture" "vgui/logos/custom/myspray"
           "$translucent" "1"
           "$vertexcolor" "1"
           "$vertexalpha" "1"
       }

5. In game, select it via:

       cl_logofile "materials/vgui/logos/custom/myspray.vtf"


Clean
=====

    make clean
